**
** IM7/8552, 134 g/m^2, 59.1% fiber volume fraction, 33% resin content
** Hand layup, autoclave cure at 180 C
** Units: N, mm, s
** Nominal ply thickness: 0.131 mm (actual may be closer to 0.125 mm)
**
** References
** 1. P. P. Camanho, P. Maimí, C. G. Dávila. Prediction of size effects in notched
**    laminates using continuum damage mechanics. Compos Sci Technol 2007;
**    67:2715–27.
** 2. P. P. Camanho, M. A. Bessa, G. Catalanotti, M. Vogler, R. Rolfes. Modeling the
**    inelastic deformation and fracture of polymer composites – Part II:
**    Smeared crack model. Mech Mater 2013;59:36–49.
** 3. A. Turon, C. G. Dávila, P. P. Camanho, and J. Costa, "An engineering
**    solution for mesh size effects in the simulation of delamination using
**    cohesive zone models," Engineering Fracture Mechanics, vol. 74, no. 10,
**    Art. no. 10, Jul. 2007, doi: 10.1016/j.engfracmech.2006.08.025.
**
** Notes
** a. alpha0 is loosely based on test observations, ref 1.
** b. Penalty stiffness is set following ref 3, eqn 7.
**    50*E2/t = 50*9080/0.131 = 3.5e6 N/mm^3, rounded to 1e6 N/mm^3
**    Values between 1e5 and 1e7 N/mm^3 have been found to give similar results
**    E3 = E2 is assumed (transverse isotropy)
**    t = ply thickness, ref 1
